Speckle Noise

Category: Other Noise Types

Description

Formula: g(x,y) = f(x,y) + f(x,y)*η(x,y), where η follows N(0, var)

Mathematical Formula

\[g(x,y) = f(x,y) + f(x,y)*\eta(x,y), where \eta follows N(0, var)\]

This noise affects the image according to the formula shown above.

Implementation

def add_speckle_noise(image, var=0.1):
    """
    Formula: g(x,y) = f(x,y) + f(x,y)*η(x,y), where η follows N(0, var)
    """
    row, col = image.shape
    noise = np.random.normal(0, np.sqrt(var), (row, col))
    noisy_img = image + image * noise
    return np.clip(noisy_img, 0, 255).astype(np.uint8), noise * 50  # Scale for visualization

Applications

  • Image processing and filtering techniques
  • Realistic texture generation in computer graphics
  • Testing and validating denoising algorithms
  • Simulation of real-world imaging conditions
